    "cover_image_url": "/assets/images/mn-gallery-006.jpg",
    "is_published": false,
    "seo_title": "Things to Do in Walker & Leech Lake | MN Lake Homes",
    "seo_description": "Explore Walker, Minnesota, and massive Leech Lake with our local guide to walleye fishing, trails, beaches, dining, and northwoods things to do.",
    "excerpt": "Walker sits on the shore of Leech Lake, one of Minnesota largest and best fishing lakes, surrounded by the Chippewa National Forest.",
    "body": "<p>The town of Walker sits on the southwest shore of Leech Lake, the third-largest lake entirely within Minnesota. Surrounded by the Chippewa National Forest, this stretch of the northwoods is legendary among anglers and beloved by families who come back every summer. The pace here is unhurried, the water is vast, and the forest presses right up to the shoreline. Here is a local guide to Walker and the wide-open waters of Leech Lake.</p><h2>World-class fishing on Leech Lake</h2><p>Leech Lake is one of Minnesota premier fishing destinations, covering more than 100,000 acres with countless bays, reefs, and shorelines. Walleye is king here, but the lake produces a wide range of fish and rewards anglers who take the time to learn its structure. Because Leech is so large, conditions can vary dramatically from one bay to the next, which is part of what makes it such an interesting lake to fish season after season.</p><ul><li>Chase trophy walleye, muskie, northern pike, and perch</li><li>Hire a local guide to learn the lake many reefs and structures</li><li>Compete in or watch the popular fishing tournaments held each year</li><li>Launch from Walker or one of the many resorts ringing the lake</li></ul><h2>Downtown Walker</h2><p>Walker is a classic northwoods town with a friendly, walkable downtown right along the lake. It is the kind of place where you can shop, grab a bite, and watch boats come and go all afternoon without ever feeling rushed. The town has held onto its authentic northwoods character, and that unpretentious, welcoming feel is a big part of why visitors return year after year.</p><ul><li>Browse local shops, galleries, and outfitters downtown</li><li>Enjoy the city beach and waterfront park on Leech Lake</li><li>Catch summer events and the well-known Moondance festival grounds nearby</li><li>Grab dinner at a supper club or lakeside restaurant in town</li></ul><h2>Trails and the Chippewa National Forest</h2><p>Walker sits in the heart of the Chippewa National Forest, so trails and wildlife are everywhere. The area is a paradise for hikers, cyclists, and anyone who loves the deep woods and quiet water. The Chippewa is one of the largest national forests in the region, and its mix of towering pines, hardwood stands, and countless small lakes gives every outing a genuine wilderness feel just minutes from town.</p><ul><li>Bike or walk the paved Paul Bunyan State Trail through Walker</li><li>Hike forest trails and watch for bald eagles and loons</li><li>Explore quiet bays and islands by kayak or canoe</li><li>Camp and picnic at national forest sites around the lake</li></ul><h2>Four-season northwoods recreation</h2><p>Walker stays active all year. When the lake freezes, the fishing does not stop, and the surrounding forest opens up to winter sports that draw visitors deep into the cold months.</p><ul><li>Ice fish for walleye and perch across Leech Lake</li><li>Ride groomed snowmobile trails through the national forest</li><li>Cross-country ski and enjoy the quiet of the winter woods</li><li>Warm up with a hearty meal at a local cafe after a day outside</li></ul><h2>Owning a piece of Leech Lake</h2><p>With so much shoreline and so many bays, Leech Lake offers everything from busy resort areas to remote, tree-lined getaways. The right spot depends on how you plan to use the lake. Our <a href='/towns'>town guides</a> can help you get to know Walker and the surrounding communities, and <a href='/find-your-lake'>Find Your Lake</a> can steer you toward the right kind of water.</p><p>Leech Lake is big and varied, so having a local expert is invaluable. <a href='/buy'>Get matched with a local agent who knows the area</a> and can help you find the right bay and shoreline on this legendary northwoods lake.</p>"
