    "title": "The Bemidji Area: Things to Do Year-Round",
    "slug": "bemidji-area-things-to-do-year-round",
    "tag": "Local Guide",
    "read_time_minutes": 8,
    "cover_image_url": "/assets/images/mn-gallery-008.jpg",
    "is_published": false,
    "seo_title": "Bemidji Area: Things to Do Year-Round | MN Lake Homes",
    "seo_description": "A year-round guide to the Bemidji, Minnesota area, from Lake Bemidji and Paul Bunyan to trails, fishing, winter sports, and downtown dining.",
    "excerpt": "Bemidji is the first city on the Mississippi and the home of Paul Bunyan, offering lakes, trails, and college-town energy in every season.",
    "body": "<p>Bemidji, Minnesota, proudly calls itself the first city on the Mississippi River, and it is best known as the legendary home of Paul Bunyan. Set on the shores of Lake Bemidji in the true northwoods, this college town blends outdoor adventure, arts, and a lively downtown. Home to Bemidji State University, it has a youthful energy you do not always find this far north, along with easy access to some of the state most iconic lakes. Here is a year-round guide to the Bemidji area.</p><h2>Lake Bemidji and area lakes</h2><p>Lake Bemidji sits right at the edge of downtown, making the water an everyday part of life here. The surrounding region is dotted with dozens more lakes, including nearby Lake Plantagenet and Cass Lake, so there is always somewhere new to explore. Having a lake right in town means you can be swimming, paddling, or fishing within minutes of leaving your front door, which is a rare luxury even in lake-rich Minnesota.</p><ul><li>Boat, fish, and swim on Lake Bemidji throughout the summer</li><li>Cast for walleye, bass, and panfish on the many surrounding lakes</li><li>Paddle the young Mississippi River as it flows through the region</li><li>Visit the Mississippi Headwaters at nearby Itasca State Park</li></ul><h2>Downtown Bemidji and Paul Bunyan</h2><p>Bemidji lakefront downtown is anchored by the iconic Paul Bunyan and Babe the Blue Ox statues. As a college town, Bemidji has a creative, energetic feel with plenty to see and do year-round, and the presence of the university keeps the arts, dining, and nightlife scenes livelier than you might expect this far north. The downtown wraps right around the lakeshore, so you are never far from the water no matter where you wander.</p><ul><li>Snap a photo with the famous Paul Bunyan and Babe statues</li><li>Browse downtown shops, galleries, and the local arts scene</li><li>Enjoy waterfront restaurants, breweries, and coffee shops</li><li>Catch live music, theater, and community events in town</li></ul><h2>Trails, parks, and outdoor recreation</h2><p>Bemidji is surrounded by state parks and forests, and it sits at the hub of an excellent trail network that draws hikers and cyclists all summer and provides quiet escapes just minutes from town.</p><ul><li>Explore Lake Bemidji State Park and its bog boardwalk</li><li>Ride the paved Paul Bunyan State Trail, which begins in Bemidji</li><li>Hike and bike through nearby forests and around area lakes</li><li>Watch for wildlife along the many woodland trails</li></ul><h2>Winter in Bemidji</h2><p>Bemidji leans into its reputation as one of the coldest cities in the country by celebrating winter rather than hiding from it. Cold-weather recreation is a way of life here, and the season brings its own festivals and traditions that locals look forward to all year. Far from slowing down when the temperature drops, the area finds new ways to get outside and enjoy the snow-covered lakes and forests.</p><ul><li>Ice fish, snowmobile, and cross-country ski across the region</li><li>Downhill ski and tube at nearby Buena Vista Ski Area</li><li>Skate, sled, and take in winter festivals and events downtown</li><li>Cheer on the local college hockey teams on a cold night</li></ul><h2>Making a home in the Bemidji area</h2><p>Between Lake Bemidji and the many lakes surrounding the city, the area offers a wide variety of shoreline, from in-town convenience to remote northwoods retreats. Figuring out which suits you is easier with local insight. Our <a href='/towns'>town guides</a> introduce the communities around Bemidji, and our <a href='/buy'>buying tools</a> show what is available right now.</p><p>Ready to explore lake living in the true northwoods? <a href='/buy'>Get matched with a local agent who knows the area</a> and can help you find the right lake and home in the Bemidji region.</p>"
